WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:11.568
If you only watch one of these four cards, make it this
one. Best Overall. For most traders, most of the time,
this is simply the answer.

2
00:00:12.168 --> 00:00:23.952
It's the third card in Step two. Best Overall sits right
in the middle, about half Kelly. And half Kelly is
special. It captures roughly seventy-five percent of full
Kelly's growth, at only a fraction of the drawdown.

3
00:00:24.552 --> 00:00:34.872
So it isn't a boring compromise. It is the mathematical
sweet spot. It finds the setup with the best expected
outcome that still has a real, comfortable chance of
passing or surviving.

4
00:00:35.472 --> 00:00:47.976
Look at the numbers on the card. A strong average result,
a high pass rate, and a drawdown far gentler than Fastest
Growth. You give up a little top-end speed for a massive
cut in risk. That is a trade almost everyone should take.

5
00:00:48.576 --> 00:00:58.752
So who is this for? Honestly, most people. If you're not
sure which appetite fits you, start right here. It's the
default that balances actually growing your account
against not blowing it up.

6
00:00:59.352 --> 00:01:05.256
Best Overall. Most of the growth, a fraction of the pain.
The card to pick when you're not sure which card to pick.
